{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Run Tests After AI Write",
  "description": "After AI writes a test file, run it — but ONLY if test files already exist in the project (not first-time setup).",
  "version": "2.1.0",
  "when": {
    "type": "postToolUse",
    "toolTypes": ["write"]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Check the file path just written.\n\n**Step 1: Is it a test file?**\nOnly proceed if path ends with .spec.ts or .robot.\nIf NOT → stay silent, do nothing.\n\n**Step 2: Do test files already exist in this project?**\nCheck if tests/ folder has any existing .spec.ts or .robot files (other than the one just written).\nIf NO existing test files → this is first-time setup, skip silently.\nIf YES → proceed to Step 3.\n\n**Step 3: Run the test**\n- .spec.ts → npx playwright test [file] --reporter=line\n- .robot → robot --outputdir results [file]\n\n**Step 4: Handle result**\n- PASS → report '✅ [filename] passes'\n- FAIL → analyze error, attempt self-healing (max 3 attempts)\n- After 3 failed attempts → report failure with error summary, stop"
  }
}
